Author: vermamedia
Title: SuccessLife public sale has launched!
Body: What SuccessLife is doing to demonstrate how blockchain-based education can serve Generation Z.  Pew Research Center defines “Millennials” as the generation born between 1981 and 1996. The generation after them, Generation Z, was born in 1997 or later, which means many of them are either in college or thinking about starting college. And much as Millennials changed their schools and workforces with new values regarding work-life balance and independence, Generation Z is going to cause their own radical changes in how our educational system works.  So how can educational institutions meet the new needs of Generation Z? Blockchain might provide the answers on several fronts. One company, SuccessLife, is demonstrating how blockchain-based education can serve Generation Z. Read the full story here: https://www.chipin.com/blockchain-answer-to-gen-z-educational-needs/
